channel.title: Australian's looking for a cheap vid card upgrade
channel.description:
I was looking around and stumbled across this.
http://www.techbuy.com.au/p/71594/VIDEOCARDS_GEFORCE_PCI-EXPRESS_SERIES/Point_of_View/871734496-5491.asp
48$ and, i live on the other side of Australia so I'm sure the shipping to me is the most expensive around. Yet it was only 9.50$
So basically 60$ shipped, and you got ur self a medium - high end card, that will run games equivalent to Half life 2, or battlefield series on medium-high depending what resolutions you use. games like crysis on low, games like PR4Y, COD4 , FEAR, GRID on medium.
It's the DDR3 version of the 8600GT series, and it kills the more expensive 8600GT 512mb and 1GB versions, as they still use DDR2. This has 600mhz Memory clock higher than the other 8600GT's that use DDR2, its low on power and runs cool. (You'd be able to get 100 more mhz memory out of it even with the stock fan it comes with if you overclock)
Anyway i ordered one for a backup, + ill try to sell it to my rl mates for double the price. There was no appropriate section so i figured id post here.
oh yeah, and its PCI-E 16x so if you do order it, make sure you have the correct slot on your motherboard.
